I read stories like this practically every day: A big thank you to the over people who have contributed something to Bun so Bun is a very large & ambitious It needs more than just one person working on it Bun’s goals are bigger than a JavaScript Introducing Oven Oven is hiring engineers Today, I’d like to make three announcements: Please meet Oven — the company that will lead Bun’s development, offer hosting, and grow Bun into an solution for Oven has raised $7m in funding led by Bucky at Kleiner Perkins with participation from Guillermo Rauch, YCombinator’s Continuity Fund and Oven is hiring ! Instructions below To say more about the company: Oven will provide incredibly fast serverless hosting & continuous integration for backend & frontend JavaScript apps — and it will be powered by It will support popular frontend frameworks like , Vite, SvelteKit, SolidStart and many more — along with backend frameworks like Express, Fastify, NestJS and The plan is to run our own servers on the edge in datacenters around the Oven will leverage integration of the entire JavaScript stack (down to the hardware) to make new things Before Oven can offer hosting, Bun needs a stable The goal: a stable release of Bun in under six months from today (August ). This is an impossible amount of work for just one Oven needs a Oven is hiring systems engineers to help design & build the next generation of internet It will be a lot of low level systems programming using Zig and C++. We re Kevin and Kevin, of We ve been close friends, ex , and ex roommates for the past 8 Both of us come from long family histories in the food industry and connections with Asian Our families run produce farms in Taiwan, operate Asian distributors and supermarkets, and sell hawker stall noodles in Our childhoods involved running around night markets and the aisles of supermarkets experiencing every sight, smell, and taste imaginable: from red bean taiyaki, mango shaved snow, to marble ramune We never forgot the fun and thrill of experiencing new foods for the first time while mixing and matching flavors on our plates to create taste As we grew older, we began to learn more about nutrition and saw the impact that unhealthy foods have had on our families as they suffered through chronic health conditions like diabetes, high blood pressure, and stomach To prevent contracting the same hereditary health conditions that our families faced, we were forced to change our lifestyles and began using macro calculators and notebooks to track calories after every Food became a chore and the magic around food began to One day, we sat around our dining table lamenting at how much we missed eating instant ramen, a nostalgic childhood food that was the first food we learned how to cook ourselves when our parents weren’t The only problem? It’s the technical term for the money you transfer from a to another retirement account, like an It’s what most people choose to do with the money they’ve saved in their account when leaving a A rollover is different to a withdrawal, which is when you pull your money out of a and pay taxes on A rollover is because your money stays in a retirement Why do people do rollovers? If you recently left a job where you had a account, it can be a good idea to roll over those savings into an IRA or a new You can also consolidate multiple or That way you can keep track of your retirement assets in one place, and make sure you’re not paying too much in What s the difference between a and an IRA? A is a type of retirement account that’s provided by You can only get it if your company provides Most of the contributions to it are from your paycheck, though sometimes an employer makes ‘matching’ When you leave the company you lose your ability to make contributions to An IRA is short for “individual retirement account”. It’s a type of account that you can open on your own, and doesn’t depend on your It’s also an account where you can transfer any savings you accumulated at a prior Think of it as a big pot that you pour your gold into over How can I do a rollover? Up Supported Actions Unlike other tools, you ll never have to manually enter a test step in Instead, our test recorder is capable of automatically detecting a wide array of user actions, letting you create a regression test simply by interacting with your Clicks Among the most common of recorded actions are When recording a test, Reflect detects the element that was clicked as well as its (x,y) coordinates relative to the of the clicked This enables us to accurately record scenarios in which the exact location of the click is One such example is Google Within Google Calendar, each day within the “Week” is represented by a single DOM This means that to accurately record a test wherein a meeting is created at a specific time of day, a click must be executed at the proper (x,y) coordinates representing that time of Click coordinates for a given test step can be viewed within the Test Step Detail view for either a previous test run or an active Mobile Taps Mobile web browsers will fire touch events rather than click events when users tap on an element on the For this reason, in mobile testing scenarios Reflect will leverage touch event APIs to record and execute taps instead of Copy to Clipboard If a click results in content being copied to the clipboard, Reflect will capture and display the copied If on a subsequent test run the click does not result in a , or if the clipboard contents do not match the expected value, the test will be marked as Hovers Reflect is the only testing tool that detects hover actions automatically and only includes the hover actions relevant to the Like all other supported actions, hover detection is completely automated and requires no action on behalf of the As you record your test, Reflect monitors for hover actions that are required for the test to be When a relevant hover action is detected, it is automatically inserted into the recorded set of test Consecutive hovers, such as hovering through primary, secondary, and tertiary navigation screens before clicking on an element, are also Reflect detects both hovers (e.g. :hover ) and Detection works across all JS Form Entry Reflect detects interactions with all form entry elements, including checkboxes, radio buttons, dropdowns, , input boxes, and The metadata associated with each form element depends on the type of form element under On the left rail, form entry test steps are organized under their common form parent (or under the body tag if no <form tag is present). WYSIWYG Elements Edits to WYSIWYG elements (enabled via the contenteditable attribute) are detected and replicated in the Reflect test These elements are typically outside of a <form element and so are recorded as standalone test Labels Form elements can optionally have an associated Labels can be defined in the HTML either as an enclosing element: < label Username: < input type = "text" name = "username" < label or as an element associated with a form element via the for attribute: < form < label for = "username" Username: < label < input type = "text" name = "username" id = "username" < form Reflect can associate an <input element to either variant of <label . When detected, the label value associated with the form element will be displayed in the test plan on the left rail as well as in the Expected Label section when clicking on a test The ‘value’ property Most form elements contain a value property, whose meaning depends on the type of form element being interacted As such, Reflect will treat the value of a form element differently depending on what element is under With form elements such as <input type="text" and <textarea , the value represents the text that’s visible within the element, and so Reflect will populate this value in the Expected Text With form elements like <input type="checkbox" , the value represents an internal value that is not visible on the page, and so in this case Reflect will populate the value in the Attributes Lastly, the <input type="file" does not have a meaningful value and the <input type="image" does not define a value property at We ignore the value property entirely for these form Scrolling scrolls are detected and will be exactly replicated in your Scrolls that occur automatically (such as visiting a link with a # fragment in the URL) are not initiated by the user and thus will not be Similarly, scrolls that occur indirectly as a result of a user action (such as clicking on a ‘Back to Top’ button) are not recorded as they are initiated from a previously recorded action (in this case, clicking ‘Back to Top’). Tailored to Support Entrepreneurs Palo Alto & San Francisco, December , — Acrew Capital today announced the closing of its first fund at $250 million, well above the top end of its original target range of $175 to $200 The firm’s approach combines a commitment to teamwork and diversity of perspective with a flexible investment The result is that Acrew can tailor a round based on the founding team’s goals and the company’s needs rather than investment Commitment to Team “We believe that successful companies are built by teams working together toward a common Venture investing should be no different,“ said Theresia Gouw, founding partner with “We consider the teams we invest in to be a part of our larger team, and our entire team is available to support the companies we invest ” The firm’s name, Acrew Capital, reflects a view that both early stage investing and company building are best accomplished by high functioning teams that constantly evolve while maintaining a core commitment to the importance of Acrew’s definition of team is broad, including everyone on the entire Acrew team as well as the founders, team members and in the companies Acrew backs, setting the firm apart in an industry that’s become increasingly less Tailored Investment Approach “We believe that our most important job is to invest in and support the best teams solving the biggest problems,” said Lauren Kolodny, founding partner with Acrew and early investor in “That’s why our model is tailored to supporting entrepreneurs and productively collaborating with other investors rather than setting strict ownership requirements and potentially missing out on the best ” Several of the team’s prior investments (Chime, Exabeam and Cato) have demonstrated that what’s most important to driving the biggest outcomes and highest returns is backing the best teams, who are well suited to solving hard As such, Acrew has formulated a flexible investing strategy intended to meet the specific and potentially unique needs of individual founding Acrew leads early stage rounds to productively collaborate with both seed funds and Acrew also joins rounds to provide a seasoned additional investor presence and diversity of perspective to help entrepreneurs in their The result is that Acrew can tailor a round based on the founding team’s goals and the company’s “When we started working this team several years ago, they structured an investment to meet our needs at a critical time for our ” said Chris Britt, CEO and of “Since the investment, they have worked as a team to support me, my and CTO, Ryan King, and our entire executive ” Built for the Decades to Come “Acrew’s goal is to build an enduring venture platform for decades to come,” said Vishal Lugani, founding partner with “In an industry where most new entrants are founded by , we believe the of our founding team lays the foundation for truly long term partnerships with founders and ” The Acrew founding team consists of Theresia Gouw , Lauren Kolodny , Mark Kraynak , Vishal Lugani , and Asad Khaliq . They previously worked alongside each other at Aspect Ventures and together combine a range of investing, operational and experience from Accel, Brown University, Google, Greycroft, and The Acrew team’s collective track record comprises more than $20B in market value created, 5 IPOs and over $1B in returns to “The Acrew team is committed to the critical principle that diverse teams drive the best outcomes, in the venture capital world and beyond,” said Melinda Gates of Pivotal “That’s why we’re delighted to support Acrew as they launch their new ” Investing Acrew pursues a approach to investing, developing conviction as a partnership, which enables each core investment Acrew makes to become a Core areas of focus and Acrew team investments include: Cybersecurity & Infrastructure Modernized (Cato Networks, Exabeam, Silverfort) Financial Services Rebuilt (Chime, Pie Insurance, Klar) Work Reimagined (Tara.ai, Divvy, Astro (acq by Slack)) Data Interconnected (CipherTrace, EvidentID, PredictHQ) Community Activated (HotelTonight, The RealReal) “The Acrew team understood our vision from the start and took a role in helping us build Exabeam into a market leader,” said Nir Polak, CEO and of Exabeam, “Their deep experience in the security domain and valuable guidance helped with everything from our initial launch to raising several follow on rounds to helping us recruit our managment ” “We’ve had a strong collaboration with Theresia and her team, and we are excited to continue with our investment in Acrew,” said Rob Salvagno, Head of Corporate Development and Cisco “Acrew’s focus on cybersecurity, enterprise, and the power of diversity are closely aligned with our own ” “We believe that depth of conviction derived from diversit

reach out to Data Security All storage of user data is encrypted at rest with strong encryption keys following industry best Matik does not store the content of customer’s data sources but instead only the minimum credentials required to access the In the event a customer’s credentials are compromised, it is their responsibility to revoke access of the credentials in the Matik app and refresh them with new Additionally, the credentials are encrypted and not viewable by Matik employees or customers once they are Matik uses Amazon Simple Storage Service (S3) and Relational Database Service (RDS) to store user data including user profiles, data credentials, and content generated from customer Both the databases in RDS and buckets in S3 have strong access controls set and are encrypted at rest using the Security Incident Detection and Management Matik takes steps to prevent unauthorized access to cloud assets (hosted by AWS) and log key events in that Matik uses the Amazon Web Application Firewall (WAF) to protect against unauthorized access to our web application servers, as well as Amazon CloudTrail to record key events to our systems, such as: logins, changes to security lists, and access to protected assets such as databases or S3 These systems are connected to an alerting system, which alert Matik’s security team in the event of anomalous In the unlikely event of a data breach, Matik will notify all affected customers no later than hours after Security Certifications SOC 2 Certified Matik has received both its SOC 2 Type I and Type II GDPR Compliant We have made significant efforts to ensure Matik is in compliance with the EU s General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). Data Backups Customer data is backed up with a regular cadence using Amazon Relational Database Service (RDS). submenu Smoking Cessation COPD Lung Cancer Additional Diagnostics Contact Open the submenu Contact Locations Laser Focal Therapy for Prostate Cancer A new path forward in prostate cancer treatment The HALO Dx Approach At HALO Dx we use Laser Focal Therapy (laser ablation) for the treatment of prostate This procedure involves placing the patient inside the MRI scanner and displaying MRI images and thermal maps on a computer A thin laser fiber is guided to the tumor and laser energy is applied to kill the cancer The temperature and the extent of the ablation zone are constantly monitored with MRI imaging, allowing HALO Dx to identify if all visible tumors have been destroyed and monitor that no important structures are Laser Focal Therapy has many advantages: Minimally invasive, ambulatory outpatient procedure (usually lasts 4 hours and patient can go home after) Rapid recovery: most patients can return to work the next day No general anesthesia required Vast majority of men have improved urination after the procedure Lower risk of side effects such as urinary incontinence, impotence and decreased bowel function compared to surgery or radiation therapy Better accuracy compared with other focal approaches, Focused Ultrasound (HIFU) Unlike other treatments, focal laser therapy does not limit the option to treat with radiation therapy or surgery if needed later Traditional approaches like radical prostatectomy (RP) have severe side effects: % risk of erectile dysfunction (impotence) % risk or urinary incontinence Dry orgasm % cancer recurrence within years, % cancer recurrence during patient’s lifetime Laser Focal Therapy - Invented by HALO! In , the tea m of Bernadette Greenwood, Chief Research Officer at Halo Diagnostics, and Roger McNichols, PhD, developed the system to perform Laser Focal The first case in the world was performed by the HALO Diagnostics team of John Feller, Greenwood, and McNichols in HALO Diagnostics released interim results from its Phase II clinical trial for prostate laser focal therapy in patients with localized prostate Over men, or older diagnosed with risk or recurrent prostate cancer, volunteered to participate in the The results are impressive: less than 1% infection, less than 1% erectile dysfunction and less than 1% incontinence – compared to conventional whole gland prostatectomy which has a risk of up to % erectile dysfunction and % urinary These results, along with a % prostate survival rate, are an encouraging development for men looking for a prostate cancer therapy option with a lower risk of side Results may vary Laser Focal Therapy: What to Expect A detailed outline of your patient journey You will receive both email and phone contact information for our medical team so that you can always reach In addition, we conduct a consultation prior to the procedure, we meet the day of the procedure, and will see you frequently in : Our team will have collected and reviewed your medical records to evaluate you for inclusion and Our surgical team will have discussed your case during Tumor Board and conducted a surgical plan based on size, number, shape and location of ablation Prior to the procedure, we will review the Informed Consent

This means that all cells in the series string are charged and discharged with the same current so that the weaker cells charge and discharge more quickly than their stronger While capacities and series resistances of new cells tend to be and , small differences between cells grow with Conventional BMS also lacks critical safety While each cell in the pack is monitored, charge and discharge functions to the cells are only controllable at the pack level, with a slow response time and no means to isolate faulty And since all of the cells are together, there exist high voltages in conductors and connectors throughout the pack, providing potential to arc and feed energy to This means that many faults, including internal and external shorts, ground faults and arc faults, are relatively unprotected and are likely to cause catastrophic Element Energy’s BMS Element Energy relies on the patented BMS (CLB ) architecture developed over more than a decade of R&D to provide software control of the charge and discharge of each individual cell to improve the safety, energy throughput and lifetime of the In this way, each cell becomes an independent energy source, Our Story - Elemental Labs Skip to content Our Story The Science Ingredients Shop Contact Us Cart Log In Our Story The Science Ingredients Shop Get Yours Our Story Health is a process Being a biochemist, athlete, and , I have always strived to improve my health and However, years ago, while I was caring for my chronically ill parents and battling my own crippling GI issues, I turned on my inner nerd, dug into the scientific literature, and ultimately adopted a ketogenic lifestyle, which eliminated most of my health Although my overall health dramatically improved, I still couldn’t get to the next level in my real passion, For years, I tinkered with my carb ratios and found minor improvements, but no matter how clean I ate or how hard I worked out… I still felt something was holding me I NEEDED MORE SALT During this time, I was working with my coaches, Tyler and Luis, the founders of When I brought up my problem, they simultaneously answered that I needed to get more electrolytes, especially I knew why getting more salt was important on a diet - the scientific literature is pretty Like many, however, I grossly underestimated just how much salt I actually I didn’t listen to them for over a year, and my results were, at best, THE BIOCHEMISTRY AT WORK When I got my electrolytes right, I felt the benefits I had more energy during , slept better, and felt my brain functioning on new I saw firsthand how easy it is to overlook the electrolyte equation, and my performance suffered for years because of And so I learned the hard way… I need to pay as much attention to my electrolytes as I do my PER OZ SERVING POPULAR PRODUCTS DIDN’T CUT IT I was frustrated with the lack of healthy options on the The hard truth is that all the existing commercially available electrolyte products are high in sugar (a keto fail) and woefully lacking in actual electrolytes (double fail). So I was forced to mix my own homebrew salt concoctions at home because getting my electrolytes right through popular electrolyte products would have added over grams of sugar to my diet per So I teamed up with Ketogains (my coaches) and Proton Enterprises (my operating partner), and we decided to do THE BEST ELECTROLYTE DRINK MIX EVER The result is a tasty electrolyte drink mix with everything you need and nothing you don’t. In terms of formulation and ingredients, we let the latest scientific literature make the decisions… yes, that means lots of salt with no sugar, fillers, gluten, or dodgy Of course, you can make this at home like I did for a number of years, but when that’s not practical, stay salty with a LMNT Recharge Born from a need, backed by science, and built for Get Yours Meet Our Team Robb Wolf Tyler Cartright Luis Villasenor Nicki Violetti James Murphy Louis Cowell Sharon Green Blake Brown We formulated LMNT Recharge based on the latest Learn More Our Story The Science Ingredients Shop Contact Us Want the latest from Elemental Labs? Stamus Networks’ Blog | Stamus Networks | I Do See About us Scirius Enterprise Careers Open Source Blog Our Blog Whitepaper: Introduction to eBPF and XDP support in Suricata 0 By Eric Leblond Posted on in Articles eBPF and XDP support is one of the latest evolutions of the Suricata engine’s performance These two technologies have been introduced recently for the Linux kernel and Suricata is one of the first well established and mature projects to make use of eBPF was introduced in the Linux kernel to be able to run user provided code safely inside the Linux kernel and XDP is running eBPF code on the network data path, as close as possible to the Network Interface The initial support for eBPF and XDP was initially available in Suricata’s , released in November , and it has been greatly enhanced in Suricata The development team at Stamus Networks, lead by Éric Leblond, has been the primary developer of eBPF and XDP support within The latest additions, list of features and potential use cases enabled by eBPF and XDP are becoming more significant, even vital, making this an opportune time to provide a high level overview for the This is the purpose of this article written by Éric Leblond and Peter Download the whitepaper: Introduction to eBPF and XDP support in Suricata Stamus Networks Stamus Networks has created a Network Traffic Analyzer (NTA), which uses network communications as a foundational data source for detecting security events, and married it with an Intrusion Detection System (IDS), which provides deep packet inspection of network traffic using a rules based The combination of these two approaches, done simultaneously in a single solution, provides a level of correlated data never previously We then added a Threat Hunting interface to allow security practitioners the ability to quickly and efficiently search through this security data to examine, validate, and resolve the security incidents that they face on a daily Suricata Suricata is a free and open source, mature, fast and robust network threat detection The Suricata engine is capable of real time intrusion detection (IDS), inline intrusion prevention (IPS), network security monitoring (NSM) and offline pcap Suricata inspects the network traffic using a powerful and extensive rules and signature language, and has powerful Lua scripting support for detection of complex Suricata’s fast paced community driven development focuses on security, usability and The Suricata project and code is owned and supported by the Open Information Security Foundation (OISF), a foundation committed to ensuring Suricata’s development and sustained success as an open source SELKS5 – The Sorceress 0 By Peter Manev Posted on in Announces SELKS 5 is out! Thank you to the whole community for your help and feedback! Thank you to all the great Open Source projects and tools mentioned below for making it possible to showcase Suricata with this new All components have been upgraded in this release to the latest version available but this is not the main SELKS is now able of doing Full Packet Capture thanks to Suricata and Moloch and benefit from an upgraded Scirius CE adding a new threat hunting Alert metadata in Scirius Hunting interface Moloch addition allows the user to investigate and explore captured data via the Moloch viewer that provide an intuitive The new Scirius threat hunting interface proposes a approach that allow to quickly find relevant alerts in a haystack and start investigation by what Features, fixes and major improvements: The whole stack has been upgraded Over new dashboards Hundreds of visualizations New Threat Hunting interface Full Packet Capture possibility Elasticsearch Logstash Kibana Moloch – The new SELKS makes use of Moloch and Moloch viewer to parse and view the full packet capture done by Moloch comes with an arsenal of tools and features on its own like: CyberChef Extremely flexible and easy to use interface for FPC drill down, filtering, search and pcap export Scirius CE Threat Hunting based on Suricata’s alerts metadata Administration, ruleset and threat hunting management Any field and action are selectable and searchable Order and set up your own threat hunting dashboard in seconds with drag and drop functionality TLS Server Name Identification HTTP UserAgent selection Easily select and filter on any metadata Suricata – latest git edition anytime SELKS scripts upgrade available now system wide in “ usr bin” Full packet Capture retention policy – thanks Joren0494 ! – SELKS health check script Debian – always thankful ! EveBox – always the latest and very thankful for your support and extremely fast bug fixing and feature addition More screenshots of SELKS 5 release SELKS is both Live and installable Network Security Management ISO based on Debian implementing and focusing on a complete and ready to use Suricata IDS IPS ecosystem with its own graphic rule Stamus Networks is a proud member of the Open Source community and SELKS is released
